        <num>413.245</num>
        <content>
          <p>Notwithstanding any other prescribed limitation of actions which might otherwise appear applicable, except those provided in , a civil action, whether brought in tort or contract, arising out of any act or omission in rendering, or failing to render, professional services for others shall be brought within one (1) year from the date of the occurrence or from the date when the cause of action was, or reasonably should have been, discovered by the party injured. Time shall not commence against a party under legal disability until removal of the disability.</p>
